Colour pattern . Body largely semitransparent covered with red chromatophores arranged in randomly oriented, narrow, short streaks; broad, white to pale-yellow, mediodorsal band extending from rostral tip to posterior margin of telson, this band interrupted between first and second, and second and third abdominal somites, respectively; rostrum, antennules, antennae, uropods and telson white; chelipeds hyaline-whitish, remaining pereiopods and pleopods colourless; eggs reddish brown (
Fig. 6 A–C
).
